parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle failure can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden acceleration
throttle stuck
inability to control the vehicle's speed
accident or near-accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can delay necessary repairs, leaving vehicles in an unsafe condition, and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealer unable to perform recall repair due to parts unavailability
delay in repair
continued risk of throttle failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the carburetor can cause the engine to stall or run rough, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or runs rough
the vehicle has difficulty starting
the engine misfires
the vehicle experiences a loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump due to corrosion can cause the engine to stall or run rough, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or runs rough
the vehicle has difficulty starting
the engine misfires
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
the fuel pump makes a loud whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, leading to loss of control, accidents, rollovers, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel is difficult to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving
the steering system makes unusual noises.
